Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.39,0:01:58.10,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.23,0:02:09.98,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,Help yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.57,0:02:11.61,Default,Psyger-0,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.41,0:02:24.04,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,What do we do now?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.04,0:02:27.59,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,Pencilgon was our smooth talker, \Nand now she's been vaporized...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.63,0:02:30.51,Default,Oikatzo,0,0,0,,That's your friend, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.51,0:02:31.96,Default,Oikatzo,0,0,0,,Do something already!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.96,0:02:34.51,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,More like the person who \Nanticipated my escape plan,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.51,0:02:37.22,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,laid an ambush, then shoved \Na friend request in my face!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.22,0:02:40.68,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,I'm still kinda walking on eggshells here!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.39,0:02:45.73,Default,Oikatzo,0,0,0,,Ah, well.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.73,0:02:49.57,Default,Oikatzo,0,0,0,,Time to show off the social \Nskills of a professional gamer!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.57,0:02:50.40,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,G'luck!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.49,0:02:59.20,Default,Psyger-0,0,0,0,,I d-do have a question \Nfor you... Sunraku-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.78,0:03:00.62,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,Y-Yes?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.29,0:03:03.25,Default,Psyger-0,0,0,0,,I... well...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.25,0:03:06.54,Default,Psyger-0,0,0,0,,Do you and... Pencilgon...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.42,0:03:09.79,Default,Psyger-0,0,0,0,,What exactly is your relationship?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.30,0:03:12.55,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.84,0:03:15.17,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,Gaming buddies?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.17,0:03:17.68,Default,Psyger-0,0,0,0,,O-Oh, is that it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.01,0:03:20.72,Default,Psyger-0,0,0,0,,Buddies... buddies...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.72,0:03:21.97,Default,Psyger-0,0,0,0,,Friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.35,0:03:27.94,Default,Psyger-0,0,0,0,,The Friend Warp timer is expiring.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.69,0:03:33.69,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,Well, seriously, \Nthanks again for helping today.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.40,0:03:35.70,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,I'll pay you back sometime!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.70,0:03:40.70,Default,Psyger-0,0,0,0,,In that case, if you ever have a minute, \NI'd love to adventure togeth—
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.83,0:03:47.75,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,Maybe I should find a game that \Nboosts your social skills.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.75,0:03:50.21,Default,Oikatzo,0,0,0,,Yeah. Wanna play {\i1}Love Clock{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.21,0:03:51.54,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,Nah, forget it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.54,0:03:53.34,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,Too much pizzeria apprenticeship trauma.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.96,0:03:54.96,Default,Oikatzo,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.96,0:03:57.34,Default,Oikatzo,0,0,0,,That creepy sword's still there.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.34,0:03:59.97,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,Probably looked too freaky to take.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.64,0:04:02.97,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,Hate to just leave it lying there, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.76,0:04:05.27,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,Ah, well.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.27,0:04:07.98,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,It's pretty creepy, but I \Nguess I'll hang onto it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.23,0:04:12.90,Default,Oikatzo,0,0,0,,Boy, I haven't felt this \Ndog-tired in a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.90,0:04:15.11,Default,Oikatzo,0,0,0,,I'm gonna sleep well tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.11,0:04:18.40,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,I'm thinking less "sleep" and more "coma."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.40,0:04:19.82,Default,Oikatzo,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.82,0:04:21.66,Default,Oikatzo,0,0,0,,Let's hit up Thirdrema, then log out.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.66,0:04:23.16,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,You said it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.63,0:04:35.42,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,What are you doing, Emul?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.72,0:04:40.68,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,I beat that baddie, no respawns needed!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.51,0:04:44.18,Default,Emul,0,0,0,,S...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.81,0:04:45.72,Default,Emul,0,0,0,,S...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.93,0:04:50.23,Default,Emul,0,0,0,,Sunraku-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.31,0:04:55.40,Default,Emul,0,0,0,,You're so amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.40,0:04:58.74,Default,Emul,0,0,0,,I was so worried!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.44,0:04:58.74,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,Excuse me?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.87,0:05:06.33,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,Hey, I'm back now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.04,0:05:08.70,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,Oh, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.75,0:05:15.46,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,Thanks for this, Emul.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.17,0:05:19.67,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,I managed to beat Wethermon \Nthe Tombguard thanks to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.64,0:05:25.35,Default,Emul,0,0,0,,S-Sunraku-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.72,0:05:29.14,Default,Emul,0,0,0,,I'm so glad!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.26,0:06:03.34,Default,Underling,0,0,0,,Chief Tsukuyogi!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.84,0:06:04.76,Default,Tsukuyogi,0,0,0,,What's the situation?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.76,0:06:07.35,Default,Underling,0,0,0,,Wethermon the Tombguard's been beaten.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.72,0:06:10.93,Default,Underling,0,0,0,,The unexpected timing has the \Nwhole company in a panic.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.93,0:06:11.85,Default,Tsukuyogi,0,0,0,,I'll bet.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.81,0:06:17.15,Default,Tsukuyogi,0,0,0,,{\i1}The expected defeat order \Nstarted with Ctarnidd,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.15,0:06:18.86,Default,Tsukuyogi,0,0,0,,{\i1}with Wethermon falling in the middle...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.86,0:06:20.99,Default,Tsukuyogi,0,0,0,,{\i1}Or perhaps the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.53,0:06:25.87,Default,Tsukuyogi,0,0,0,,{\i1}I thought I'd be able to enjoy my wife's \Nhome cooking for the first time in two days,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.87,0:06:28.28,Default,Tsukuyogi,0,0,0,,{\i1}but I'm getting dragged back to the office...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.62,0:06:29.99,Default,Tsukuyogi,0,0,0,,Is Tsukuri in the down below?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.99,0:06:33.62,Default,Underling,0,0,0,,Yes, likely holed up as usual.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.62,0:06:37.79,Default,Underling,0,0,0,,But I heard Amachi-san was \Nheading off in that direction...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.17,0:06:38.84,Default,Underling,0,0,0,,So...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.84,0:06:40.05,Default,Tsukuyogi,0,0,0,,I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.55,0:06:42.01,Default,Tsukuyogi,0,0,0,,This is part of the job.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.26,0:06:51.35,Default,Tsukuyogi,0,0,0,,{\i1}It's empty?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.35,0:06:53.35,Default,Tsukuyogi,0,0,0,,{\i1}D-Damn it...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.35,0:06:54.52,Default,Tsukuyogi,0,0,0,,{\i1}I'm going in unarmed.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.65,0:06:57.94,Default,Tsukuyogi,0,0,0,,Do you carry stomach medicine, by chance?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.94,0:06:58.73,Default,Underling,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.73,0:07:01.03,Default,Underling,0,0,0,,Oh... no, I don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.11,0:07:04.40,Default,Tsukuyogi,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.79,0:07:19.63,Default,Voice,0,0,0,,{\i1}Employee ID recognized.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.96,0:07:21.96,Default,Voice,0,0,0,,{\i1}Please input code.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.88,0:07:25.22,Default,Voice,0,0,0,,{\i1}Code recognized.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.59,0:07:27.09,Default,Voice,0,0,0,,{\i1}Please confirm fingerprints.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.43,0:07:30.93,Default,Voice,0,0,0,,{\i1}Fingerprints recognized.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.93,0:07:32.64,Default,Voice,0,0,0,,{\i1}Now undergoing retinal scan.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.64,0:07:34.64,Default,Voice,0,0,0,,{\i1}Please place your face near the sensor.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.64,0:07:35.85,Default,Amachi,0,0,0,,This is bullshit!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.85,0:07:37.52,Default,Amachi,0,0,0,,Freaking open up already!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.65,0:07:39.77,Default,Voice,0,0,0,,Retina print recognized.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.66,0:07:53.62,Default,Amachi,0,0,0,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.00,0:08:05.55,Default,Amachi,0,0,0,,Wethermon's been defeated.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.55,0:08:10.76,Default,Amachi,0,0,0,,Was it not you who said at the rate things \Nwere going no one would beat him in ten years?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.76,0:08:13.47,Default,Tsukuri,0,0,0,,I said {\i1}Ashura Kai{\i0} couldn't do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.77,0:08:19.60,Default,Amachi,0,0,0,,I wasn't expecting them to bring \Nthe Reward Scales into it...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.60,0:08:22.15,Default,Amachi,0,0,0,,{\an8}But they didn't use any glitches or cheats.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.15,0:08:24.23,Default,Amachi,0,0,0,,{\an8}It's impossible to complain about the result.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.98,0:08:27.32,Default,Tsukuri,0,0,0,,Impossible to complain?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.70,0:08:28.99,Default,Tsukuri,0,0,0,,Don't give me that!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.99,0:08:34.16,Default,Tsukuri,0,0,0,,You're the one who nerfed Wethermon \Nin that utterly disgusting way!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.16,0:08:36.91,Default,Tsukuri,0,0,0,,Admit it was a mistake! Right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.91,0:08:38.12,Default,Amachi,0,0,0,,Oh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.12,0:08:42.67,Default,Amachi,0,0,0,,That's because no one could ever beat him \Nwith the original stats you gave him!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.67,0:08:46.21,Default,Tsukuri,0,0,0,,That's because Wethermon's supposed \Nto be really, {\i1}really{\i1}, really strong!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.21,0:08:48.05,Default,Tsukuri,0,0,0,,He's the greatest hero of the Divinity!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.05,0:08:51.43,Default,Tsukuri,0,0,0,,But your stupid worries \Nabout stupid game balance
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.43,0:08:54.64,Default,Tsukuri,0,0,0,,are ruining my carefully designed story concepts!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.64,0:08:58.64,Default,Amachi,0,0,0,,You can't tie story progress flags \Nto an unbeatable monster!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.64,0:09:00.52,Default,Amachi,0,0,0,,Are you nuts or something?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.52,0:09:02.19,Default,Tsukuri,0,0,0,,How dare you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.19,0:09:06.36,Default,Tsukuri,0,0,0,,You're a parasite feeding on the \Nleftovers of my beautiful world!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.36,0:09:07.03,Default,Amachi,0,0,0,,What was that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.40,0:09:12.16,Default,Amachi,0,0,0,,You couldn't balance your \Npreshesh little world,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.16,0:09:15.41,Default,Amachi,0,0,0,,which is why I had to shtep \Nin and do it for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.41,0:09:16.04,Default,Amachi,0,0,0,,Dumbass!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.62,0:09:20.58,Default,Amachi,0,0,0,,Your dandruff is terrible!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.58,0:09:22.54,Default,Tsukuri,0,0,0,,So's yours!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.54,0:09:24.00,Default,Amachi,0,0,0,,I had a shower two days ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.00,0:09:26.71,Default,Tsukuri,0,0,0,,And I had one three days ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.51,0:09:30.13,Default,Tsukuyogi,0,0,0,,{\i1}My stomach hurts.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.13,0:09:33.09,Default,Tsukuyogi,0,0,0,,{\i1}But I can't let this scare me off.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.93,0:09:37.06,Default,Tsukuyogi,0,0,0,,That's enough, both of you!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.06,0:09:39.35,Default,Tsukuyogi,0,0,0,,How long are you going \Nto fight like children?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.35,0:09:40.89,Default,Amachi,0,0,0,,You shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.85,0:09:45.52,Default,Tsukuyogi,0,0,0,,{\i1}Stomach... hurts!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.86,0:09:55.87,Default,Tsukuyogi,0,0,0,,{\i1}Utopia's crown jewel is the fully \Nimmersive VR game, {\i0}Shangri-La Frontier{\i1}.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.78,0:10:00.29,Default,Tsukuyogi,0,0,0,,{\i1}Tsukuyo Tsukuri designed the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.29,0:10:05.46,Default,Tsukuyogi,0,0,0,,{\i1}and Ritsu Amachi balanced it to \Nwhere it could function as a game.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.84,0:10:08.05,Default,Tsukuyogi,0,0,0,,{\i1}Who would have dreamed the
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.05,0:10:12.17,Default,Tsukuyogi,0,0,0,,{\i1}core development staff would \Nbe fighting like preschoolers?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.93,0:10:17.56,Default,Tsukuyogi,0,0,0,,{\i1}I already have so much to do to \Nprepare for what's coming up...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.56,0:10:19.68,Default,Tsukuyogi,0,0,0,,{\i1}And yet these two, every single time...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.27,0:10:22.31,Default,Tsukuyogi,0,0,0,,Calm down.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.98,0:10:25.98,Default,Tsukuyogi,0,0,0,,I'm the only one who can pacify them.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.36,0:10:27.31,Default,Tsukuyogi,0,0,0,,{\i1}Still...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.69,0:10:31.32,Default,Tsukuyogi,0,0,0,,{\i1}To think {\i0}Shangri-La Frontier{\i1}'s \Nstory would have kicked off
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.74,0:10:34.57,Default,Tsukuyogi,0,0,0,,{\i1}in this extremely unexpected way...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.70,0:10:38.66,Default,Tsukuyogi,0,0,0,,H-Hey, you two! At least go take a shower!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.66,0:10:41.50,Default,Tsukuri/Amachi,0,0,0,,Shut up, you Pomade-stinking four-eyes!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.97,0:11:03.77,Default,Rei,0,0,0,,I took a big step... a big step today!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.18,0:11:06.23,Default,Rei,0,0,0,,Hizutome-kun asked me to come to him...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.02,0:11:11.86,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,Come, stand by my side.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.11,0:11:15.36,Default,Rei,0,0,0,,And he gave me all those presents...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.61,0:11:17.28,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,{\an8}For you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.70,0:11:23.37,Default,Rei,0,0,0,,W-We'll keep getting closer, and in time,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.37,0:11:26.46,Default,Rei,0,0,0,,maybe we'll get closer... \Nin the real world...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.17,0:11:28.21,Default,Rei,0,0,0,,Squee!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.35,0:11:41.01,Default,Rakuro,0,0,0,,All right...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.14,0:11:45.60,Default,Rakuro,0,0,0,,Time to get going!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.69,0:11:50.56,Default,Rakuro,0,0,0,,I still gotta tally up all my gains.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.70,0:12:07.41,Default,Emul,0,0,0,,M-My dadd—
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.41,0:12:09.75,Default,Emul,0,0,0,,The boss wants to see you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.17,0:12:11.96,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,How long have you been crying?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.96,0:12:17.72,Default,Vysache,0,0,0,,Mind if I ask you a question, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.30,0:12:21.51,Default,Vysache,0,0,0,,How'd you like that stubborn old fool?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.85,0:12:24.10,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,Well, Aniki Vash...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.72,0:12:26.64,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,Wethermon was quite strong indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.06,0:12:31.36,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,That Woodmage thing couldn't even compare.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.61,0:12:35.99,Default,Vysache,0,0,0,,I'll bet.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.53,0:12:38.49,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,{\i1}If not for my experience playing trash games
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.49,0:12:40.32,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,{\i1}where unreasonable attacks were the norm,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.32,0:12:42.66,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,{\i1}it'd have been over before it started.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.37,0:12:46.00,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,{\i1}Hey, Emul-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.00,0:12:47.83,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,{\i1}Where do you think you're blowing your nose?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.75,0:12:56.34,Default,Vysache,0,0,0,,Did he depart this world satisfied?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.05,0:12:59.84,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,He said it was a job well done.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.18,0:13:01.84,Default,Vysache,0,0,0,,Ah, excellent.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.22,0:13:09.81,Default,Vysache,0,0,0,,Cultivate and open the way...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.48,0:13:13.36,Default,Vysache,0,0,0,,Perhaps the time has come.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.15,0:13:15.61,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,The time...?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.82,0:13:22.57,Default,Vysache,0,0,0,,Would you like to know the \Ntruth of this world, son?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.62,0:13:30.33,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,I would be honored.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.58,0:13:37.80,Default,Vysache,0,0,0,,Then there's a little something \NI'd like you to do for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.80,0:13:39.34,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,Do for you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.13,0:13:42.68,Default,Vysache,0,0,0,,Just bring me a few items.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.68,0:13:43.59,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.14,0:13:46.68,Default,Vysache,0,0,0,,There's a process to these things, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.18,0:13:51.19,Default,Vysache,0,0,0,,Once you've done it, \NI'll tell you the truths of this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.77,0:13:58.53,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,{\i1}Oh, come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.53,0:14:03.74,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,{\i1}I was all hyped up about kicking off \Nmy bonus unique scenario, Vorpal Epic,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.74,0:14:05.62,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,{\i1}and it's a freaking fetch quest?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.24,0:14:07.58,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,{\i1}Well, fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.58,0:14:10.87,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,{\i1}That's how these things always start, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.87,0:14:13.83,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,Let's see... Items needed...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.83,0:14:20.26,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,Receiver Delta, Positioner Delta, \NTransmitter Delta...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.80,0:14:24.43,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,I think I get the gist, but where do \NI even start looking for these things?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.80,0:14:27.60,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,Surely you're not going \Nto send me out blind...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.97,0:14:29.18,Default,Vysache,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.18,0:14:32.85,Default,Vysache,0,0,0,,Check out a place called \Nthe Lightless Barrens.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.14,0:14:34.77,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.77,0:14:36.48,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,Lightless Barrens?
Dialogue: 1,0:14:38.86,0:14:41.53,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,I guess it's nowhere near Thirdrema, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.86,0:14:46.57,Default,Vysache,0,0,0,,You won't find it on a chintzy map like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.99,0:14:51.79,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,Guess I'll check Peatz's shop next.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.16,0:14:53.29,Default,Vysache,0,0,0,,Well, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.71,0:14:56.83,Default,Vysache,0,0,0,,I guess I'll go wait \Npatiently for your return.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.83,0:14:58.21,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,H-Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.21,0:14:59.84,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,Can't you give me any more info?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.59,0:15:03.01,Default,Vysache,0,0,0,,As long as you're not too great a fool,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.34,0:15:04.76,Default,Vysache,0,0,0,,you should find it soon enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.52,0:15:15.81,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,Maybe it's in an area \Nway ahead of where I am?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.27,0:15:19.86,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,Unique scenarios do kinda seem \Nlike endgame content, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.44,0:15:21.61,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,Guess it makes sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.61,0:15:23.74,Default,Emul,0,0,0,,It seems it may be quite a long journey!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.57,0:15:27.36,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,Sweet, naive Emul...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.36,0:15:29.20,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,You might be surprised.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.24,0:15:33.91,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,Hell yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.91,0:15:37.12,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,My level freaking exploded \Nfrom that Wethermon fight!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.12,0:15:40.13,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,I got a flood of new skills \Nand evolved skills, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.13,0:15:42.21,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,Guess it'll be time for a new \Nvisit to the Skill Garden!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.21,0:15:44.01,Default,Emul,0,0,0,,Well done, indeed!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.01,0:15:48.59,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,A power boost like this'll have me \Nskating through the game for a while!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.59,0:15:50.47,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,But wait, there's more!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.01,0:15:53.72,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,Yes, don't forget...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.72,0:15:56.39,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,The Wethermon battle loot!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.39,0:15:58.60,Default,Emul,0,0,0,,The time has come!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.60,0:16:05.15,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,They wouldn't put me through all that \Neffort for a totally lame payoff, right?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.15,0:16:06.61,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,Gimme that good stuff!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.12,0:16:11.41,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,What the heck's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.41,0:16:13.99,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,"Tome of Truth: The Tombguard."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.70,0:16:18.79,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,Oh, it's just a detailed rundown \Nof Wethermon's backstory.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.21,0:16:21.25,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,I can read that stuff later.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.50,0:16:24.42,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,C'mon, give me something I can use!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.38,0:16:31.51,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,Let's see... "Clear Sky Skillbook"?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.39,0:16:34.85,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,Clear Sky Skillbook...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.85,0:16:40.56,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,"A digital record of sword techniques \Nleft by a Divinity-era swordsmaster."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.15,0:16:43.44,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,"The strikes recorded within \Ncan cleave the heavens,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.44,0:16:46.40,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,pierce the earth, and clear dark clouds."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.78,0:16:50.49,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,"Divinity equipment is required \Nto decipher and master them."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.82,0:16:54.58,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,Wait, isn't "Clear Sky" that \Narray of skills Wethermon used?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.58,0:16:56.25,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,What? What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.79,0:16:59.83,Default,Emul,0,0,0,,What is it, Sunraku-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.25,0:17:04.75,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,I can freaking learn Wethermon's skills?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.92,0:17:09.72,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,You kidding me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.18,0:17:14.39,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,Which means...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.72,0:17:17.64,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,I might be able to learn "Sky Clear", too?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.98,0:17:21.02,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,This is too freaking good!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.02,0:17:25.32,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,It says I need Divinity equipment, \Nso it might be a while...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.32,0:17:27.03,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,But this is gonna be great!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.03,0:17:28.07,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,Right, Emul?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.65,0:17:32.53,Default,Emul,0,0,0,,I thought you were gonna \Nrub my cheeks off...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.78,0:17:34.03,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,Hell yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.03,0:17:36.41,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,Let's keep up the pace!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.41,0:17:38.45,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,And for my last piece of loot!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.54,0:17:42.42,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,Hey, it's an accessory!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.79,0:17:46.13,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,I'll bet it gives a pretty sweet stat boost!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.13,0:17:47.92,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,{\an8}Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.92,0:17:50.59,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,{\an8}"Inventoria Key."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.59,0:17:54.18,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,{\an8}"It is both the door and the \Nkey to a storage space,"
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.18,0:17:59.77,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,{\an8}"a special bracelet worn only by a \Nselect few, even during the Divinity."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.60,0:18:03.81,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,"Even if the wearer is player-killed,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.81,0:18:09.28,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,neither the accessory nor the items \Ninside the storage space can be stolen."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.28,0:18:10.53,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,Hey, pretty good!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.53,0:18:15.53,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,"Provides portable access \Nto an expandable space."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.37,0:18:22.16,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,"Synchronizes with anatomical data to \Nfuse and become a part of the user."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.87,0:18:27.00,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,"Acts as a warehouse with infinite storage"?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.67,0:18:34.76,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,So it's like an item box you can stuff \Nanything smaller than 50 meters in?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.34,0:18:40.47,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,I can also spend some MP to transport \Ninto the storage space itself, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.60,0:18:47.40,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,Not as cool as I'd hoped, \Nbut let's give it a try.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.41,0:18:58.95,Default,Emul,0,0,0,,H-He disappeared!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.12,0:19:08.79,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,So this is my storage space... huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.55,0:19:16.47,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,H-Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.05,0:19:20.51,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,{\an8}I know I was asking for \Nstuff I could use, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.19,0:19:34.32,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,What the hell is this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.04,0:19:53.63,Default,Pencilgon,0,0,0,,I'm pretty much destitute now,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.96,0:19:58.51,Default,Pencilgon,0,0,0,,but I went hard on bartering \Nand managed to get them.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.93,0:20:03.52,Default,Pencilgon,0,0,0,,I'll have something much \Nnicer the next time I come.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.97,0:20:05.68,Default,Pencilgon,0,0,0,,I hope you'll give me some leeway this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.65,0:20:14.65,Default,Pencilgon,0,0,0,,These flowers stay in bloom \Nfor five minutes, then die.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.49,0:20:18.66,Default,Pencilgon,0,0,0,,But if you pick them before that happens \Nand put them in your inventory,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.66,0:20:21.87,Default,Pencilgon,0,0,0,,the flowers stays in bloom, they say.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.66,0:20:25.87,Default,Pencilgon,0,0,0,,They live for a moment, \Nthen remain for eternity...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.37,0:20:29.33,Default,Pencilgon,0,0,0,,The flower's name reflects \Nthat— "Setsunatowa."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.25,0:20:32.42,Default,Pencilgon,0,0,0,,Perfect for you and me, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.50,0:20:36.55,Default,Pencilgon,0,0,0,,You called yourself a copy,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.01,0:20:39.47,Default,Pencilgon,0,0,0,,but as far as I'm concerned, \Nyou were the original.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.80,0:20:41.43,Default,Pencilgon,0,0,0,,The real deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.93,0:20:52.86,Flashback,Setsuna,0,0,0,,If you wish to know of your roots... \Nof the truth of this world...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.23,0:20:57.19,Flashback,Setsuna,0,0,0,,Seek out "Bahamut."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.32,0:21:01.53,Default,Pencilgon,0,0,0,,The truth of this world, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.24,0:21:09.71,Default,Pencilgon,0,0,0,,Well, I'd originally meant to quit {\i1}SLF {\i0}\Nafter I beat Wethermon the Tombguard...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.75,0:21:14.21,Default,Pencilgon,0,0,0,,But all right, Set-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.59,0:21:25.18,Default,Pencilgon,0,0,0,,{\i1}Whatever this Bahamut thing is,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.85,0:21:29.27,Default,Pencilgon,0,0,0,,{\i1}I'll get it to cough up \Nall the secrets it holds.
